race.comment: TALLINGAS PRINCE (5) doesn't win out of turn but was in the finish last time when beaten a neck into third at Tatura. Doesn't have to improve much to get the verdict this time. AZEOLA (2) is close to a win after a string of minor placings, the latest when third after she got a long way back in the run at Swan Hill. Gets in well with the claim and is suitably placed so anticipating another big run. TOSEN GLORY (6) has been in the placings his past two starts, finishing third at Hamilton last time out. Best figures stack up nicely. DASHING DONKEY (3) hasn't been as effective in his last two but was a convincing winner three back at Leeton. Has to be some hope if he can recapture that form. PARABELLUM (7) was much better last start at Grenfell when in the placings. In the mix if she can build off that over this longer trip.
